<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Seminar on Air Transport Held in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A South Asian regional
seminar was held here today to find out ways to solve the problems
in the air transport sector in the region.
</P>
<P>
The one-day seminar, organized by the SAARC Technical Committee
on Transport, was also aimed at coordinating efforts to develop
air transport between countries in the region and mobilizing human
resources in the field.
</P>
<P>
A senior Nepali civil aviation official at the seminar
underlined the need to adopt a common air policy in South Asian
countries for the development of tourism in the region.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was attended by 24 representatives from the SAARC
(South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation) countries --
Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri
Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
