<HEADLINE> Over 230 Gymnasts to Compete in Aisan Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, Central China, September 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 230
Gymnasts from the region will take part in the First Asian
Gymnastics and Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships slated for Friday
to Sunday, organizers said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With three days to go, gymnasts from a dozen of countries and
regions have arrived Changsha and concentrated on training at the
two gymnasiums before vying for over 30 gold medals.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizing committee of the championships,
participants are from Hong Kong, Indonesia, India, Iran, Japan,
Kazakhstan, Kirghizstan, South Korea, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait,
Malaysia, the Philippines, the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea, Thailand, Chinese Taipei, Vietnam, Uzbekistan and host
China.
</P>
<P>
The championships feature the senior and junior events, which
are the first major international competitions held in Changsha,
capital of Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province has made progress in the sports in the past ten
years with cultivating a group of ace gymnasts, such as Olympic
uneven bar gold medalist Lu Li and silver medalist Li Jingg in
1992.
</P>
<P>
Hunan has now two spare-time gymnastics schools and 10 training
sites for the sports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
