<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets St. Petersburg Chief Legislator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT PETERSBURG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chairman of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) met
here this afternoon with Yuri A. Kravtsov, chairman of the
Legislative Assembly of Saint-Petersburg.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived from Moscow this morning, said the CPPCC
actively supports cooperation between local governments of the two
countries so as to the enrich their overall bilateral strategic
and cooperative relations of partnership.
</P>
<P>
Citing the fact that the Legislative Assembly of
Saint-Petersburg has given positive support to the city's
cooperation with China, he stressed that the cooperation between
the localities has become a major part of friendship.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Kravtsov said China is a great country, and the
people of Saint Petersburg have always cherished profound
friendship with the Chinese people and appreciated the
achievements China has made in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Li's current visit to Saint-Petersburg, he added, will further
promote the city's relationship with China.
</P>
<P>
Saint-Petersburg and Shanghai are the first couple of
sister-cities of the two countries. 
</P>
