<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Power Station Shares Sold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
province today sold part of its shares in the New Shaanxi Weihe
Power Station to a Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong China Travel Service Group Company will have 51
percent of the shares of the thermal power station, worth 2.754
billion yuan, for the next 20 years. When the contract expires,
the Hong Kong company will return the shares to the provincial
Power Construction Investment and Development Corporation.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest overseas-funded project in the province and
also the first of its kind in the country's power sector.
</P>
<P>
The installed capacity of the station, built last year, is 1.2
million kw. The value of the station's total assets has reached
5.4 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
