<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 14:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 PKK Rebels Killed in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Eleven rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in eastern
Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the large-scale military operations
started Monday in fighting with a group of about 250 PKK
elements who were encircled in Kinzir Forest in Hozat town,
Tunceli province.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted security officials as saying that the air
and ground military operations will continue until all the PKK
rebels in this region are wiped out.
</P>
<P>
The PKK militants were discovered hiding in the forest when a
wounded PKK rebel inadvertently revealed the hiding place to the
Turkish security forces.
</P>
<P>
The rugged province has been the scene of operations of such
kind against the separatist group in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a guerrilla war for self-rule in
southeastern Turkey, which has claimed more than 21,000 lives in
the past 12 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
