<HEADLINE> 20 Import Items to Be Under Compulsory Check-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Beginning on October 1, 20
import items will be listed for compulsory examination by the
China Commodity Inspection Bureau (CCIB).
</P>
<P>
In the future, only those commodities bearing CCIB license
labels may be imported, according to CCIB sources.
</P>
<P>
On September 4, 1995, CCIB and the State Foreign Economic and
Trade Commission issued a circular that named the second group of
commodities affected by the safety and quality licensing system.
</P>
<P>
The 20 items include washing machines, vacuums, appliances for
grooming hair and skin, electric water heaters, electric ovens,
microwave ovens, electric pots, electric irons, electric food
processors, fluid heaters, videotape recorders, audio equipment,
personal computers, monitors, switch-mains, printers, electric
tools, low-voltage electric appliances and electric welding
machines.
</P>
<P>
Since the circular was issued, CCIB has received more than 800
applications from over 180 factories based in 27 foreign countries
and regions. So far, CCIB has issued over 500 safety and quality
licenses to these applicants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
