<HEADLINE> Judo Coach Arrested for Sexual Assault in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A 56-year-old judo coach was
arrested last week in the southern French city of Bordeaux for
sexually assaulting two of his pupils aged from 11 to 13, Agence
France Presse quoted quoted official sources as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Bernard Sudre, administrative director of the judo club of
Vieux Bordeaux, however denied the accusation by the families of
two girls that he abused them from late 1995 to 1996.
</P>
<P>
Judo is one of the most popular sports among French children,
who join thousands of judo clubs across the country and have judo
classes in schools. 
</P>
