<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Olympians to Be in Asian Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, Central China, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China will
send 12 men and women gymnasts, including five Atlanta Olympians,
to compete in the Asian Gymnastics and Rhythmic Gymnastics
Championships starting on Friday in Changsha.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese Gymnastics Association, the roster of
the country's mage gymnasts are Shen Jian, Fan Hongbin -- members
of the Chinese Olympic runners-up team -- Cheng Liang and Huang
Xu, while the female team is composed of three Olympians Ji Liya,
Kui Yuanyuan and Mao Yanling, and Zhou Duan.
</P>
<P>
China was fourth in the women's team event at Atlanta Olympic
Games this summer.
</P>
<P>
China's boys Lu Yufu and Zhao Ji and girls Jin Ying and Sang
Lan will take part in the junior competitions.
</P>
<P>
The gymnastics championships feature the senior men's and
women's team events, apparatus finals and junior men's and women's
all-around events and apparatus finals from Fridy to Sunday.
</P>
