<HEADLINE> Mid-Autumn Reception Held to Call for Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Participants at a reception
hosted today by the China Council for the Promotion of Peaceful
Reunification said they hope for early reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The reception was held to celebrate the Mid-Autumn Festival,
which is considered a festival for family reunion and which falls
on September 27 this year.
</P>
<P>
Present were chairmen of the council Qian Weichang, Wang
Guangying, Lu Jiaxi, Wan Guoquan, Zhang Kehui and Wu Guozhen, and
its advisers Lin Liyun, Jing Shuping, Jia Yibin, as well as guests
from the mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Presiding over the reception was Wang Guangying, who is also
vice-chairman of the National People's Congress Standing
Committee. In his speech, Wang extended Mid-Autumn Festival
greetings to 21 million Taiwan people and overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Other speakers included were Qian Weichang, vice-chairman of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National
Committee, and Liu Yandong, deputy head of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee's United Front Work Department.
</P>
<P>
They urged the Taiwan authorities to cease separatist
activities and to cooperate with the mainland on accelerating the
process of reunification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
