<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Little Change in EU's Industrial Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production of the
European Union (EU) in the second quarter this year rose 0.1
percent over the first quarter, according to Eurostat, the EU's
statistical office here today.
</P>
<P>
However, it fell by a similar rate if compared to the fourth
quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
The rise could be attributed to both seasonal factors and
fluctuations, the office said.
</P>
<P>
In the period, orders for export were up by 1.2 percent,
following a 0.4 percent rise in the first quarter while domestic
orders down by 0.1 percent, following a rise of 1.5 percent in the
first quarter.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat also notes that industrial production in the United
States increased by 1.3 percent and that in Japan by 0.3 percent
during the same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
