<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Beer Drive Gives Australia Malt A Boost </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The booming Asian beer
market was a sleeping giant for Australian malt and beer
manufacturers, one of the country's biggest malt producers said
today.
</P>
<P>
Bill Gill, managing director of the Adelaide Malting Company,
Australia's third largest malting company and the biggest supplier
of the ingredient to Southeast Asia, told reporters that beer
consumption is growing faster in Asia than anywhere in the world.
</P>
<P>
Industry statistics showed beer consumption in China, already
near the same rate as that of the United states, rose by up to 10
percent last year with no sign of abating in the near future, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"As a leading supplier based in Australia we are right on the
doorstep of the Asian operations of some of the world's largest
brewers, because of this we are in the best possible position to
capture a larger proportion of sales."
</P>
<P>
"The Asian market would present Australian producers with a
wealth of opportunities into the next century," he said, adding
that the estimated market for Australian malt would double in the
next 10 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
