<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zaire Protests Rwanda for "Aggression" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Zaire's Foreign Ministry today
summoned Rwandan ambassador in Kinshasa to protest against
Rwanda's "aggression" after heavy fightings Sunday night and
Monday in areas between Bukavu, eastern Zaire, and Cyangugu,
southwest Rwanda, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Zaire's Vice Prime Minister Kamanda Wa Kamanda
pointed out in a speech that Rwanda should be responsible for the
fightings.
</P>
<P>
He accused Rwanda of "providing assistance to armed bands of
Banyamurenge" -- the ethnic Tutsis, and said that the Banyamurenge
militias were infiltrating into Zairean territory to launch
"operations of destabilizaiton."
</P>
<P>
However, he refrained from making any threat to Rwanda and
Burundi in his speech.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month Zaire alleged that Rwanda and Burundi were
"fomenting troubles" in the region of Uvira, but met rejection
from both of them.
</P>
<P>
It launched a large-scale hunting of "Banyamurenge" Tutsis in
the hills near the Burundian border.
</P>
<P>
About one million Rwandan Hutu refugees have been living in
refugee camps in eastern Zaire, after they fled Rwanda following a
genocide committed by Hutu army and militias against Tutsis and
Hutu people in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
