<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Soccer Star to Be Awarded as Goal King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September (Xinhua) -- Soccer star Ferenc Puskas has
been honored with the record for the most goals in Hungarian
championship history, the International Federation of Football
History and Statistics (IFFHS) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
IFFHS, based in Wiesbaden, Germany, said Puskas, the
69-year-old former Honved and Real Madrid star, netted 512 goals
in his 528 national championship games.
</P>
<P>
The federation studied records going back to 1888 and Puskas,
playing for Honved and Real Madrid between 1943 and 1966, was the
only player to have scored over 500 goals in national championship
games, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Pele may scored more than 1,200 goals in his career, but
because Brazilian national championships didn't start until 1970,
most of Pele's goals didn't make the record books.
</P>
<P>
The official presentation of Puskas's award, along with another
nine all-time greatest scorers will be November 2 in Leipzig,
Germany.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 14:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Donor Countries Pledge 14 Million Dollars to UNRWA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Donor countries have pledged 14
million U.S. dollars in support of the U.N. Relief Works Agency
(UNRWA) to help it tackle a cash shortage threatening services to
millions of Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by UNRWA Commissioner General Peter
Hansen who called for a meeting of host governments and donor
countries to discuss the agency's deficit and current financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which opened here on Monday, agreed on the
importance of the UNRWA's role in the Middle East and reaffirm
support for the agency to ensure its continued and uninterrupted
services to the Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's Crown Prince Hassan made a speech at the meeting,
saying that the role of the UNRWA must be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
He told delegates that stability in the region requires
international cooperation to assist the U.N. body.
</P>
<P>
According to the crown prince, the total number of the
Palestinian refugees in the Middle East amounts to more than 3.2
million, of whom 41 percent are hosted by Jordan and 38 percent in
the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The services Jordan provided to the refugees cost the kingdom
more than 300 million dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
Robert Hopkins, director of UNRWA's operations, announced
Monday at the meeting that the American delegation had pledged an
additional 5 million dollars to the agency's budget which
currently suffers a 45 million-dollar deficit.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. annual donation to the world body is 70 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
