<HEADLINE> Gas Leakage Kills Six In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Six died from a gas leakage
in a skyscraper apartment in the New Territory and one was in
critical condition, reports the local evening broadcast.
</P>
<P>
Three men, one women and two children were proved dead after
being sent to hospital this morning. Doctors believed that the six
were suffocated to death for lack of oxygen since no wound was
found on their bodies.
</P>
<P>
Police found the victims at around eight o'clock this morning
after the gas alarm rang. The leakage from a gas cylinder in the
kitchen led to the death. They suspected that homicide and suicide
could be involved in the case, which is now under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The dead were four adults aged between 30 and 50, a boy at the
age of six and a three-year-old girl.  
</P>
</TEXT>
