<HEADLINE> Reception Marks Sino-Yemeni Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A reception marking the 40th
anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Yemeni diplomatic ties
was held in Beijing this evening.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries (CPAFFC), along with the China-Yemen Friendship
Association (CYFA), hosted the event.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
China's National People's Congress, attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
The CYFA President, Zhang Canming, said that China and Yemen
are ancient countries in Asia, and that the friendship between the
two peoples dates back to the far-distant past.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both countries are also developing countries, and
that the two peoples have conducted sincere cooperation in many
fields and established bonds of deep friendship.
</P>
<P>
Yemen is one of the first Arab nations to establish diplomatic
ties with China, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that cooperation in every area between the two
countries has thrived over the past 40 years, and he expressed the
belief that the friendship between the two peoples will continue
to grow.
</P>
<P>
Yemen's Ambassador to China, Mohammed Hadi Awad, said that
Yemen and China have experienced the same sort of difficulties in
their histories.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, both hold that state-to-state relations should be
developed on the basis of the principle of "non-interference into
each other's internal affairs, and mutual respect for each other's
sovereignty," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"The Yemeni government supports China in realizing its
reunification and recognizes that Taiwan is an inalienable part of
China," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that the friendly cooperative relations
between the two countries will continue to develop.
</P>
<P>
Also present were Li Chengren, deputy head of the International
Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China, the CPAFFC Vice-President Xu Qun, and guests from other
departments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
