<HEADLINE> U.N. Withdraws Staff From Zairean Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations agencies
started today to evacuate staff from the eastern Zairean town of
Bukavu following heavy gunfire overnight between the Rwandan army
and Zairean forces.
</P>
<P>
Brenda Barton, a spokeswoman for the U.N. World Food Program
(WFP) office based in the Kenyan capital of Nairobi, said the
first plane with eight passengers left Bukavu for Nairobi at noon
and a C-130 transport plane would leave later today with 43 more
passengers.
</P>
<P>
