<HEADLINE> ADB Helps China Acquire Advanced Thermal Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) approved a two-million-US-dollar assistance loan here today
to help China acquire advanced and cleaner power technology.
</P>
<P>
The loan is expected to finance the requisite consultancy
services to prepare preliminary designs and tender documents for
the proposed Anhui Fuyang thermal power plant, which will involve
the installation of two 600-megawatt units based on supercritical
steam technology.
</P>
<P>
The proposed power plant will be one of the first in the
country to use the technology. The loan will help Chinese
engineers to become familiar with this advanced and cleaner
technology.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the plant will improve the electricity supply
in Fuyang city administrative region and also benefit the
consumers of the East China power network. 
