<HEADLINE> China Welcomes US Investors and Traders: Vice Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing today told the Illinois State Trade Delegation, headed by
Governor Jim Edgar, that China welcomes American companies to
invest in the country and conduct trade here.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes investment in China from big businesses,
such as Motorola, as well as cooperation with small and medium-sized
enterprises, Li said in a meeting this afternoon with the group.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, the economies of China and the US are
complementary, and show great potential for economic cooperation.
He said he hopes the two sides will work more closely with each
other to fully explore their opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier stressed that only when the two countries
respect dissimilarities in each other's culture and history can
cooperation be effective.
</P>
<P>
Edgar echoed Li's views by saying that differences in political
opinions should not influence economic cooperation. In fact, he
said, the establishment of stronger trade ties between US and
China might help solve political issues.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the US guests on China's major areas for
foreign investment. He said he believes that the forthcoming visit
by Wu Yi, minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, to
the Unites States will enhance trade ties between the two
countries. 
</P>
