<HEADLINE> China Preserves Minority Nationalities' Operas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A research center designed to
preserve the operas of more than a dozen minority nationalities
opened today in the Central University of Nationalities in western
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li Peilun, secretary general of the China Society For Minority
Nationality Operas and director of the center, said that a
national survey conducted two years ago found that operas of the
minority nationalities are nearly extinct, and that fewer people
are participating in them, particularly youngsters.
</P>
<P>
The 62-year-old Hui nationality scholar said that the
unsophisticated operas created by the groups are valuable to the
research of the minority nationalities' origin, history and
culture.
</P>
<P>
Li said that in addition to its research work, the center will
establish a department of national operas in the university within
the next two or three years. The university is China's major
educational venue for the young people of the 55 minority
nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the new center opened today with a national opera
class of 18 students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
