<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
rose slightly amid rejuvenated interest in local resources shares
today.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index climbed 9.5 points to 2228.7 points.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers said that the rally was quite surprising. The
Australian stock market fell sharply in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
But they said that the market was still weak in the eve of the
meeting of the decision making arm of the Federal Reserve of the
United States. Investors were divided on whether the Fed would
raise or cut short-term interest rates after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
