<HEADLINE> Sudan Denies Launching Air Raids on Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sudanese army has
denied a Ugandan accusation that Sudanese warplanes dropped
bombs over an Ugandan area close to the border between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers today quoted Sudanese army spokesman Mohammed
el Senoussi as saying that such reports are untrue.
</P>
<P>
He said that the reports are intended to foil the peace efforts
by Iran to secure a reconciliation between Sudan and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan senior defense official Amama Mbabazi said in
Kampala Sunday night that two Sudanese warplanes bombed the
Ugandan town of Moyo Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
According to an Iran-sponsored agreement concluded between
Sudan and Uganda on September 9, the two countries should halt
mutual media campaigns and keep away from supporting each other's
opposition elements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
