<HEADLINE> Reception of Dalai Lama to Affect Sino-Australian Ties: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Shen Guofang said here today that the Australian
Government's reception of the Dalai Lama would have an impact on
Sino-Australian relations.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference this afternoon, Shen said that China has
"stressed time after time that the Dalai Lama is more a political
figure in exile than a religious one, who engages himself in
activities aiming at splitting China."
</P>
<P>
The reception and meetings between Australian government
leaders and the Dalai have constituted "an interference in China's
internal affairs," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
This will surely cast a shadow over Sino-Australian relations
by affecting bilateral political relations, he said, adding that
it is also unavoidable to affect trade relations.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that the Australian government can adopt a
correct attitude towards the issue and will not interfere in
China's internal affairs.  
</P>
