<HEADLINE> Shelling Kills 7 In S. Mogadishu's Refugee Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Seven Somalis, including a
boy and two women, were killed and four others were wounded when
a mortar round landed on a refugee camp in South Mogadishu last
night.
</P>
<P>
The Shabelle Refugee Camp was situated near the former command
control of Hussein Mohamed Aidid, son of the late warlord General
Mohamed Farah Aidid. Six of the deceased had died right on the
spot while another died at Digfer hospital.
</P>
<P>
The incident followed an exchange of small arms and heavy
mortar shells in Bosnia Vicinity last night between the
militiamen of Hussein Mohamed Aidid and those of his rival, Osman
Hassan Ali Atto.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the renewed shooting is not yet known. Both
sides accused the other of firing the first mortar shells in the
area.
</P>
<P>
The shelling lasted until this morning. Heavy machine guns
were heard but there has been no ground and street battle
attacks.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 200 refugees in the camp have moved into vacated
buildings for shelter. Some of the terrified refugees attended
the funeral of their fellow refugees this morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
