<HEADLINE> HK Company Invests in South China Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China Merchants China
Direct Investments Limited (CMCDI) announced that it has entered
into a contract to invest 10 million US dollars for a 16.8 percent
 stake in the 114- kilometer Zhangzhou section of National Highway
 No.324 in South China.
</P>
<P>
The road section, comprising three toll stations, is now
operated by a Sino-foreign joint venture, Zhangzhou Tongda Road
Development Co. Ltd. Reconstruction work was completed at the end
 of 1995.
</P>
<P>
National Highway No.324 is one of the major traffic routes in
southern China. The road section connects Fujian province to
Guangdong province and is the main route for the transportation of
 supplies between the two provinces.
</P>
<P>
CMCDI will be co-investing with China Insurance Group
Investment Co. Ltd. in this project and they together will acquire
 a 25.2 percent equity interest from the original foreign partner
of the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
This is CMCDI's second toll highway project after its
investment of 5 million US dollars in the Luomei section to the
west of Guangdong of National Highway No.324.
</P>
<P>
CMCDI is jointly managed by China Merchants Holdings (Hong
Kong) Company Limited and Victor Chu China Investment
Limited. 
</P>
