<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNHCR Excludes 20 Rwandans From Refugee Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) announced today that it was excluding from
refugee status 20 Rwandans indicted by the International Criminal
Tribunal for Rwanda in connection with the 1994 genocide in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The UNHCR said it was also urging governments to take the same
measure if these Rwandans were to seek asylum in their countries.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time that the exclusions were announced by
the international body on the basis of the tribunal's indictments.
</P>
<P>
The 20 Rwandans are believed to be among those behind the
planning and execution of the genocide in which more than 500,000
Rwandans were killed.
</P>
<P>
Some of these Rwandans are in the custody of the tribunal.
Three were arraigned in the Tanzanian town of Arusha in June. The
others are known to be in Europe and other African countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
