<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Fair of China-made Dress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is to host a dress
fair featuring China-made clothes designed for autumn and winter.
</P>
<P>
The fair, to be held from September 25 to October 3 at the
National Agriculture Exhibition Center, is the first to be named
for national products only. Organized by China's Dress Designing
Center (Group), it will display products of 200 state-renowned
domestic garment enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is also a part of the Beijing tour of an exhibition for
prize-winning designs in the "Dress for 21st Century Fashion
Design Competition".
</P>
<P>
The competition was held to mark the 50th birthday of the
United Nations. The exhibition includes tours in Paris, New York,
Tokyo as well as Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The organizers of the fair said that China's clothing industry
has developed quickly in the past five years, with total sales
amounting to 450 billion yuan (about 53 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
China now has 47,000 garment enterprises, which are able to
produce 8.7 billion garments every year.
</P>
<P>
The country has put 2.3 billion yuan (about 277 million US
dollars) into garment enterprises to update their technology, and
brought up over 40 enterprises, each of those has annual sales and
profits of more than 100 million and 10 million yuan,
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
