<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Retail Sales on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
total retail sales rose seven percent to about 18.9 billion HK dollars
(2.44 billion US dollars) in July this year over a year earlier,
according to the provisional figures released by the Census and
Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total retail sales increased by three percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a year ago, sales of motor vehicles increased
substantially by 34 percent in value and 32 percent in volume.
Sales of other consumer durable goods also went up by 10 percent
in value and nine percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales of food, alcoholic drinks and tobacco went up by five
percent in value, albeit virtually no change in volume.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, sales of clothing and footwear and sales in
department stores increased by five percent and two percent in value
but decreased by one percent and three percent in volume respectively.
</P>
<P>
Compared with June 1996, total retail sales in July 1996
increased by eight percent in value and nine percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Total retail sales from January to July this year rose six
percent in value and one percent in volume compared with the
corresponding period of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
