<HEADLINE> Nujiang River "Grand Canyon" a Hot Tourist Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Nujiang River Canyon,
known as the "Grand Canyon of the Orient" has become a hot
tourist attraction as increasing travelers and adventurers swarm
in.
</P>
<P>
Located in the west of Yunnan Province, southwest China, the
Nujiang River Canyon is grand and steep because of the swift
Nujiang River, the perilous Biluo Mountain and the Gaoligong
Mountain on each bank of the river.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan section of the Nujiang River Canyon is 621
kilometers long and 3,000 meters deep, as compared with the Grand
Canyon in Colorado which is 440 kilometers long and 1,839 meters
deep.
</P>
<P>
Tourists visiting the Nujiang Grand Canyon can not only see the
canyon itself, but can also be exposed to the rich ethnic culture
and folklore of the local Lisu, Bai, Nu, Dulong, Jingpo and
Tibetan ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The primeval forests, waterfalls and rivers are also tourist
highlights.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to modern highways, it takes ten hours for tourists to
get to the canyon from Kunming, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Last year, over 194,000 Chinese and overseas tourists visited
the canyon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
