<HEADLINE> 36 Rebels killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 24 (Xinhua)-- 36 Tamil rebels were killed
and over 100 others injured in government troops' fresh attacks on
Monday in Kilinochchi District, Northern province of Sri Lanka,
according to Military sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that on the government side, 15 soldiers were
 killed in action and 21 wounded.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, rebels on two occasions attempted to land a number
of boats on the east coast near Vettilaikerny. Air force
helicopters and naval crafts deployed in the area engaged the
rebel boats and destroyed them. However, casualties suffered by
the Tamil rebels in the incidents are not available, The sources
said.  
