<HEADLINE> Zambian Cashewnut Farmers Urged for Local </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Zambian cashewnut farmers
have been challenged to form a strong body to process their
products.
</P>
<P>
The Times of Zambia newspaper today quoted bell marketing
enterprises marketing manager Frank Baines as saying in northern
Zambia that it is important for the local cashewnut farmers to
organize themselves into the strong body to represent their
interests.
</P>
<P>
The local cashewnut industry has collapsed and the farmers
have nowhere to sell their products in the absence of a local
industry to absorb their raw materials, the local newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 cashewnut farmers in Western Province could
form a strong association to mobilize funds and set up a local
processing industry, Baines said.
</P>
<P>
Farmers can benefit a lot from the processing industry, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Cashew, among other things, is used to manufacture paints,
detergents and some chemical products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
