<HEADLINE> Iran Asks for More Aids to Iraqi Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian government has
asked for more relief assistance to the Iraqi Kurdish refugees
being sheltered in three Iranian provinces.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry said in a statement published in local
press today that the aid given by the United Nations is not
enough and the refugees will soon face new problems as the cold
season is approaching.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) said
last week that it had granted an aid of 3.08 million U.S. dollars
to cover the basic needs of some 40,000 new Iraqi Kurdish
refugees for a span of three months.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government expressed thanks to the UNHCR for its
relief assistance. But it said that three million dollars given by
the organization is only a fraction of what Iran has already spent
on refugees.
</P>
<P>
It said that the U.N. relief assistance is far from sufficient
in meeting the massive needs of some 60,000 refugees, who would
have to suffer cold and rainy season soon.
</P>
<P>
Iran said that it has spent more than 25 billion rials
(about 6 million dollars) on sheltering Kurdish refugees from
northern Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
