<HEADLINE> Fair of Medical Herbs Profitable in Bozhou City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Deals worth 660 million yuan
were made during a recent traditional Chinese medical herb fair in
Bozhou City in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 16,000 domestic and overseas business people took
part in the five-day event.
</P>
<P>
The planting, processing and use of traditional Chinese medical
herbs date back nearly 4,000 years ago. In recent years, trade in
traditional Chinese medicines has been revitalized, contributing
much to local economies.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,500 households in 600 villages around the city are
engaged in growing and processing of medical herbs.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, local people paid 40 million yuan (4.8 million US
dollars) in state taxes from medical herbs. 
</P>
