<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Agree to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen and his Russian counterpart Yevgeny Primakov agreed
today that their two countries should strengthen cooperation in
the field of international affairs.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting held in New York, both Qian and Primakov held the
view that the two countries have had close cooperation in the
international affairs as well as the U.N. affairs, and have made
satisfactory achievements.
</P>
<P>
"They agree to strengthen such kind of relationship," said
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Cui Tiankai.
</P>
<P>
Both foreign ministers are satisfied with the recent years'
development of bilateral relationship, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
"They believe that China and Russia should enhance their
friendship and build a strategic cooperative partnership oriented
toward the 21st century, which will conform to the interests of
the two peoples and benefit peace and stability of the region as
well as the world at large," Cui added.
</P>
<P>
Qian invited Primakov to visit China later this year. Primakov
said he was looking forward to the visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
