<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 07:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Warns of Conflict with US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Iran has warned that it will
conflict with the United States throughout the Persian Gulf up
to the Sea of Oman if it is attacked.
</P>
<P>
Major General Mohsen Rezaee, Commander of the Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps, said "if the slightest problem breaks
out for us or the slightest pressure is exerted on us, we will
disregard all restrictions and become engaged in conflict with
the U.S. throughout the Persian Gulf up to the Sea of Oman,
making them repent their deeds."
</P>
<P>
The strong-worded statement by the Iranian major general was
carried on the frontpage of today's English-language daily Tehran
Times.
</P>
<P>
Rezaee said that if Americans were sure that "they could wage
a war against us in a limited framework, and readily bring us
under their control, they would have so far done so."
</P>
<P>
"But they well know that if they did so, we would extend the
war, making them repent," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Americans strive to keep the region
insecure and tension-ridden in order to rationalize their
presence in the region, and at times threaten Iran, but their
threats are empty.
</P>
<P>
"Americans know that if the slightest incident occurs in the
region, it may lead to a massive war, which might spill over
other places, with the Americans losing the game." he said.
</P>
<P>
As to the Israeli threat to Iran, he said, Israel has been
confronting Iran for the past five or six years. "If Israel
wants to take action against us, it will use its air force, and
in response we will not restrict ourselves to the air. We will
decide where and how to respond to Israel."
</P>
<P>
The commander said that "What is certain is we have prepared
ourselves for these threats and any confrontation."
</P>
<P>
However, he ruled out the possibility of an all-out war in
the region, saying that none of the regional countries are now
ready for a big war.
</P>
<P>
"Given the economic, political and social situation in the
region, the outbreak of such a war is unlikely," he added.
</P>
<P>
"If the U.S. does not intervene in the region and the
regional countries become united, no incident will occur in the
region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian commander rejected claims that the growth of
Iran's military build-up and defensive capabilities pose a
threat to regional countries.
</P>
<P>
"We have never waged war against any country, nor will we do
so except against aggressors," he said. "our power is a
deterrent to aggressors."
</P>
<P>
He said that "we believe that the growth of our defensive
capabilities will not be a threat to others. We will not employ
this power in a way that would be detrimental to others."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
