<HEADLINE> Zambia's Elections Office Ready to Operate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Elections Office (EO) of
Zambia has already put in place all election logistics such as
ballot boxes and election materials while waiting for President
Frederick Chiluba's announcement of the election date.
</P>
<P>
EO actiing director Joel Sikazwe made the announcement after
presenting a paper on "the role of the elections office" to a
political reporting workshop in Lusaka on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The workshop participants were drawn from the Zambia News
Agency, the Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation, the Zambia
Daily Mail, Radio Phoenix and Radio Christian Voice.
</P>
<P>
Sikazwe ruled out the use of transparent ballot boxes during
the elections as was demanded by some opposition parties, saying
there was no need for such boxes.
</P>
<P>
The EO would use the ballot boxes that were used in the 1991
polls as they would be opened, inspected on the spot in presence
of election observers, candidates or their polling agents before
being sealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
