<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tangshan Calls off 199 Unqualified Foreign-funded Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Department of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation in Tangshan City, Hebei Province,
has revoked the licenses of 199 unqualified Sino-foreign joint
ventures, the "International Business daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Those on the list included 48 ventures operating with their
licenses which had been rescinded before a city-wide inspection,
seven unregistered firms, five awaiting revocation as a result of
disputes between Chinese and foreign partners, 57 which had failed
to provide promised investment and 73 which had no licenses, no
funds or workshops.
</P>
<P>
The revoked ventures involved a total investment of 510 million
US dollars, a combined registered capital of 386 million dollars,
and a combined contractual foreign investment of 212 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Up to June this year, the city has approved 796 foreign-funded
enterprises, 309 of which have gone into operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
