<HEADLINE> Japanese Motor Company to Launch New Touring Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Nissan Motor Company
will launch a new touring station wagon for domestic market on
October 3.
</P>
<P>
According to the Kyodo News Service, besides an antilock
braking system and dual air bag supplemental restraint systems,
the new cars also adopt electronic torque split four-wheel-drive
systems, which will provide "superb driving stability on all sorts
of road surfaces along with sure-footed traction when starting off
on icy or snow-covered roads."
</P>
<P>
The new Stagea models will be priced at 2.27 million Japanese
yen (about 20,636 U.S. dollars) to 3.16 million yen (about 28,727
dollars) in the Tokyo area, said Nissan Company, which aims to
sell 5,000 Stageas per month. 
</P>
