<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Cotton Output To Exceed Target This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's cotton output in
the fiscal year of 1995-1996 will reach 10.6 million bales,
exceeding the target of 9.5 million bales.
</P>
<P>
The official Associated Press of Pakistan reported today that
it will show a significant increase of 21.7 percent over the
preceding fiscal year's crop of 8.7 million bales.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the increase mainly to favorable weather
conditions and extensive efforts by the government to boost the
production.
</P>
<P>
Areas under cotton crop increased by nearly 13 percent from
2.65 million hectares in 1994-95 to 3.00 million hectares in
1995-96.  
</P>
</TEXT>
