<HEADLINE> Swedish Telecom Company Launchs Joint Venture in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson, the largest
telecommunications supplier in Sweden, has set up a joint venture
in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, to
manufacture advanced program-controlled switching systems.
</P>
<P>
The plant, located in one of Nanjing's economic development
zones, has a production area of 13,000 square meters, and is the
largest joint venture Ericsson has ever launched in China, said
the journal "China Telecom World".
</P>
<P>
The plant is estimated to generate an output value of 1.5
billion yuan annually, and most of its products, the AXE-10
switching machines, will be sold abroad.
</P>
<P>
As one of the most sophisticated digital switching systems, the
AXE-10 is used in 140 countries, boasting a combined capacity of
100 million lines across the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
