<HEADLINE> Turkish Police Seizes 14 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized 14
kilograms of pure heroin in a drugs bust in eastern Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the Turkish police intercepted a car in
Tatvan town of Bitlis province and found the heroin in 29 parcels
hidden in the unconspicuous places in the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The police detained two suspected drug smugglers, but
did not disclose when the heroin was seized.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Turkish police confiscated some 3.5 tons of
Heroin, 17.4 tons of hashish, nearly one ton of base morphine,
121 kilograms of opium, 75 kilograms of cocaine, 53.3 tons of
anhydride acrid, which accounted for 22 percent of the drugs seized
in the world. 
</P>
