<HEADLINE> Government Troops Fight against Encircled PKK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces
today started large-scale military operations with the support
of armored vehicles in fighting with about 250 rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
The PKK revels were encircled Monday in Kinir Forest in
eastern Turkey, according to the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted reliable sources as saying that fighter
planes and Cobra helicopters that took off from Erhac air base in
Malatya province participated in the military operations against
the group of the encircled PKK rebels in Hozat town of
Tunceli province.
</P>
<P>
The sources said he could not disclose the death toll of the
encircled rebels for the time being.
</P>
<P>
The PKK militants were discovered to be hiding in the forest
when a wounded PKK rebel inadvertently revealed the hiding place
to the Turkish security forces.
</P>
<P>
The rugged province has been the scene of previous operations
of such kind against the separatist group in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a guerrilla war for self-rule,
which has claimed over 21,000 lives in southeastern Turkey for
the past 12 years. 
