<HEADLINE> PLA General Holds Talks With Zimbabwean Army Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the
general staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), held
talks today with Zimbabwean Defence Forces Commander Musungwa Gava
Zvinavashe.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China treasures the long-term friendship between
people of the two countries and development of friendly
co-operation ties with Zimbabwe in all areas.
</P>
<P>
He said at the meeting in Beijing: "There is a profound
friendship between the Chinese and Zimbabwean armed forces. We are
willing to make joint efforts with Zimbabwean armed forces to
develop the friendly co-operative relations between the two
armies, based on equality and mutual benefit."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government unswervingly pursues the independent
diplomatic policy of peace. It is one of the basic points of the
Chinese foreign policy to strengthen unity and co-operation with
African countries and other developing countries, Fu said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's successful visit
to six African countries last May, including Zimbabwe, was of
great historic significance. He added that China supports all
African countries establishing their own political systems, ways
of development and values, based on their respective conditions,
and supports them to solve regional conflicts independently and
peacefully, and to increasingly and equally involve themselves in
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Zvinavashe thanked the Chinese government for the selfless aid
to Zimbabwe in its struggles for national liberation, and its
economic development after independence.
</P>
<P>
Zvinavashe reiterated that Zimbabwean government adheres to
"one China" stance, and recognizes Taiwan as an inalienable part
of China's territory.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed general Fu on the situation of Zimbabwe and
southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Before the talks, Fu hosted a welcome ceremony in his honor.
Zvinavashe arrived in Beijing Sunday at the invitation of
Fu. Zvinavashe is the first Zimbabwean Defence Forces Commander to
visit China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
