<HEADLINE> "Spark Program" Achievements Fair Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A major fair showing off a
decade's achievements in China's state "Spark Program" opened in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The government-backed Spark Program is China's first nationwide
plan to encourage economic development in rural areas with the
help of science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of delegations from China's 30 provinces, municipalities
and autonomous regions, and more than 1,000 rural enterprises, are
participating in the five-day fair sponsored by the State Science
and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
The fair introduces Spark Program's achievements in regional
development, fostering rural pillar industries, aid-the-poor with
promotion of science and technology, development of resources in
central and western parts of China and farmer training.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also introduces a number of major research
achievements and new technology projects made by Chinese
scientists and technicians in agriculture, forestry, animal
husbandry and fishing.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists have developed 470 new varieties of seeds
and over 1,000 new farming technologies during the past five
years. 
</P>
