Japanese woman to reach the Wimbleton semifinals this year.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old tennis star has won the Japan Open women's
singles title four times in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
In April, the right-hander recorded her biggest victory of her
career by defeating world top player Steffi Graf in the Federation
Cup match in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
At the Wimbleton semifinals, the Japanese woman was defeated by
Graf.
</P>
<P>
Date started playing tennis at the age of six and turned
professional in 1989. 
