<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Faces Shortage of Academics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is facing acute
shortage of highly qualified personnel to work for the country in
the coming years, a local press report said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, about 1,000 professors, associate
professors, as well as doctors and associate doctors get retired
every year, but only 500 qualified people are available to replace
them.
</P>
<P>
Most of the highly-qualified teachers at colleges and
universities specializing in social and natural sciences are over
50 years old, said the Education and Training Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry regarded the lack of funds as the main cause for
the academic shortage.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Vietnam's brightest young academics preferred to
work for foreign companies, which made the shortage more serious.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
