<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Puts in Order Market Agents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- All market go-between
organizations in special economic zone Shenzhen, are to be
separated from government institutions in a campaign to rectify
market order.
</P>
<P>
Also as part of the effort government employees will not be
allowed to be involved as market agents.
</P>
<P>
As a pioneer for China's socialist market economy, Shenzhen
neighboring Hong Kong, now boasts over 3,300 market go-between
organizations, employing over 35,000 people, latest statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
While playing an increasingly important role in bridging ties
between the market with enterprises and the government, problems
have been found among as well as the malpractice of taking
advantage of government ties, resulting in unfair competition.
</P>
<P>
In its determination to maintain market order, the municipal
government has decided to carry out an over-all check on the
go-between market, covering job introductions, real estate
dealing, assets assessment, and law firms.
</P>
<P>
Existing relevant rules and regulations will also be subject to
re-examination.  
</P>
</TEXT>
