<HEADLINE> Highest Temperature in Late September in 61 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's capital Beijing
basked in its hottest late September for 61 years, with
yesterday's temperature reaching 32.5 degrees centigrade.
</P>
<P>
It was the second highest late September temperature in
Beijing since 1915 when the city started its own records of
temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday's high was only 0.2 degrees centigrade lower than the
highest recorded temperature in the city on September 22, 1935.
</P>
<P>
Meteorological experts contributed the hot weather to high
pressure which has been controlling the area since last
weekend. Due to the warm air mass, Beijing has been clear, less
windy and enjoyed much sunshine.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasters said today's highest temperature would be
29 degrees centigrade. Meteorological experts estimated a drop in
temperature tomorrow, as a cold current is moving toward Beijing
from central Mongolia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
