submarine and its crew including the dead bodies at once," said
the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of South Korean Defense Ministry on Monday
described the incident as a "military provocation" and rejected
the DPRK's demand for the return of the submarine.
</P>
<P>
South Korean officials said that in the past few days 11 DPRK
people were found to have killed themselves, nine were killed by
South Korean troops and one was captured alive. Five are
reportedly still at large. 
