<HEADLINE> China Investment Symposium Opens in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on China's policy
on foreign investment, sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xinhua, deputy minister of the MFTEC, briefed French
participants on the economic situation and foreign investment in
China in his keynote speech at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign funded enterprises have actually invested a total of
155 billion U.S. dollars in China and the majority of joint
ventures and solely foreign funded enterprises are well managed,"
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
With the continuous growth of Sino-French economic and trade
relations in recent years, France had become the fourth largest
European investor in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yves Galland, minister delegate to the French Ministry of
Economy and Finance in charge of finance and foreign trade, said
developing relations with China was a priority of the French
government.
</P>
<P>
France was determined to seize the "huge opportunity" of the
Chinese market, he said.
</P>
<P>
France encouraged its businessmen to invest in China, because
China had created sound conditions for foreign investment, he
said. He noted that China had brought inflation under control while
ensuring the continuous and fast expansion of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Galland said China's foreign currency reserves and the
purchasing power of its consumers were quickly increasing.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the Chinese side would do a better job in
helping foreign enterprises obtain more accurate market
information in China and learn more about the Chinese laws and
regulations.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 delegates from China's provinces attended the
symposium. They brought with them a long list of 640 projects that
are open to foreign investment. 
</P>
