<HEADLINE> Security Railing For Sri Lanka's Ancient Temple </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 24 (Xinhua)-- A massive iron railing is to
be constructed round the outer perimeter of Sri Lanka's ancient
Sri Maha Bodhi Temple in Anuradhapura town of North Central
province, according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
It is in this premises that the Bo tree grew from a sapling of
the Bo tree in India under which Lord Buddha had meditated.
Regularly thousands of devotees worship here. The Bo tree is over
2,300 years old.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 1 million rupees (17,800 US dollars) has been
allocated for the construction of the railing which is considered
necessary as it is a prime target of the rebels of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam who made a plan to attack this sacred place
recently, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The North Central Provincial Council will provide funds of up
to 89,000 US dollars to set a metal detector gate at the main
entrance.
</P>
<P>
At present, a high security network keeps a 24 hour vigil at
the temple and all pilgrims are subjected to body search.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the sources added that road blocks and check
points have been set up at all approach roads to the temple.
</P>
</TEXT>
