the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
But Renat Akchrin, top heart surgeon and head of the operation
team, said last weekend that the surgery to improve the blood
supply to Yeltsin might be delayed for six to eight weeks and
there was a risk of the operation being cancelled altogether if
Yeltsin's health did not permit it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
