<HEADLINE> Investments Rise in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Direct foreign investments
in Brazil totaled 5.4 billion U.S. dollars during the past eight
months, a 55.2 percent increase over the same period last year,
said the Central Bank today.
</P>
<P>
During the January-August period, liquid investments amounted
to 3.4 billion dollars, an increase of 50 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's international currency reserves reached 59.6 billion
dollars in August, an 11.4 percent increase over that of January.
</P>
<P>
Since January, Brazil has paid six billion dollars in interest
abroad, while interest payments for the same period last year were
22.3 percent lower.
</P>
<P>
The bank also said that stock market resources had increased.
</P>
