<HEADLINE> Sino-American Auto Meters Joint Venture Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Delco Electronics
and Instrumentation, a joint venture between Delco Electronics
Company of General Motors Corporation of the United States, and
Changjiang Meters and Instruments Plant of Shanghai, has gone into
production.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the new company will produce and
market mechanical, electro-mechanical, electronic meters and
instruments, and related electronic components for motor vehicles,
as well as produce temperature control boards for vehicles.
</P>
<P>
For the time being the products of the joint venture will only
be sold on the Chinese market.  The joint venture has also set up
business offices in Shanghai and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Changjiang Meters and Instruments Plant of Shanghai is the sole
supplier for localized meters and instruments needed in the
production of Shanghai Santana cars and Santana 2000-type cars,
which are produced by Shanghai Volkswagen Corporation, a
Sino-German joint venture. The plant is also one of the four
designated enterprises for producing auto meters and instruments
by the Ministry of Machine-building Industry.
</P>
<P>
Delco Company is a world famous enterprise for producing auto
meters and electronics, with annual sales volumes amounting to 5.6
billion US dollars, ranking at the top among auto electronics
manufacturers in the world.
</P>
<P>
According to William Spelman, president of Delco Electronics
Asian-Pacific Region, Shanghai Delco Electronics and
Instrumentation is the American company's first investment in
China, and the company is also planning to invest money and start
businesses in other areas of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
