<HEADLINE> Works of Late Adventurist Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A collection of diaries and
travelogues written by late Chinese expeditionary Yu Chunshun has
been published.
</P>
<P>
"An Adventurist in China -- Yu Chunshun Walks Across Tibet", is
the only work of Yu who was found dead in June after he walked
alone across the Lake Lop Nur area in Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region. The book has been published by Shanghai Culture and Art
Press.
</P>
<P>
In July 1988 the Chinese adventurist bid farewell to his
hometown of Shanghai and started his lone expedition across the
country.
</P>
<P>
In the following eight years, Yu traveled 84,000 kilometers and
visited 33 ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The book records, in 288,000 words, his high risk experiences
in Qinghai-Tibetan Plateau from 1991-92.  
</P>
