<HEADLINE> Taowei Railway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- With the completion of the
Taowei Railway, an integrated railway transportation network has
been formed in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The railway from Taocun to Weihai, is 137.5 kilometers long
and has 14 stations along its route. Money for the construction of
the railway was raised by Weihai City itself.
</P>
<P>
Goods from 5,000 railway stations in China can now be directly
transported to stations along the Taowei Railway.
</P>
<P>
The railway is expected to carry 1.2 million tons of cargo this
year, and is targeted to carry four to five million tons at the
end of this century.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, passengers in Weihai will be able to travel to
Shandong's provincial capital of Ji'nan and Beijing by the
railway. 
</P>
