<HEADLINE> Hebei Speeds Up Aviation Transportation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hubei
Province is flying high after seeing a take-off in its air
transport system.
</P>
<P>
Until recently the province saw a slow development in aviation
transport, only starting its first civilian flight in 1984.
</P>
<P>
But since last year the province has stepped up development of
air travel with the opening of Shijiazhuang Airport. The airport
is listed as one of the alternative airports for Beijing Capital
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial aviation officials, Hebei has opened 17
domestic air routes linking the province with 19 major Chinese
cities, and also an air route to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
By the end of October, Shijiazhuang Airport will open four more
domestic air routes to Kunming, Nanjing, Xiamen and Qingdao, and
chartered flights to Russia are expected to begin later this year.
</P>
<P>
Not far from Beijing and Tianjin, two largest cities in the
country, Hebei is one of the major agriculture production bases
and rich in mineral and tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this century, Hubei will transform Shijiazhuang
Airport into an international airport and build or expand four
other major airports in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
