<HEADLINE> Great Achievement of Township-run Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The turnover of township-run
enterprises in northwest China's Shaanxi Province is expected to
reach 100 billion yuan by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
It had already exceeded 68 billion yuan by the end of August,
said local officials.
</P>
<P>
Sales volumes of the enterprises make up 76 percent of the
rural economy and their industrial output value accounts for 46
percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
According to Quan Zhichang, director of a provincial bureau in
charge of township-run enterprises, nine counties have each
generated turnovers of over two billion yuan, 20 counties' have
reached over one billion yuan each, even 26 villages have
generated more than 100 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The success has been due to the popularization of new
technology. The township-run enterprises often make use of the
latest technology offered by universities and scientific research
institutions. Now some of the enterprises' products are exported
to the Unites States, Japan and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises made great efforts to carry out enterprise
system reforms, and over 8,400 of them have established a
share-holding system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
