<HEADLINE> France to Help Bosnia Destroy Heavy Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A French military delegation
arrived in Bosnia today to help the Serbs and the Muslim-Croat
Federation to destroy their excessive heavy weapons in accordance
with an agreement signed in Vienna in June by Bosnia, Croatia and
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
"The Republika Srspka" has agreed to let France help it destroy
the excessive part of its heavy armaments, which will be carried
out under the supervision of the Organization of Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), said French Foreign Ministry
vice-spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
Bosnian Serbs, Muslims and Croats are given 16 months to
destroy their excessive heavy weapons, according to the agreement
which was formalized by the United Nations at a conference of
examination of peace accords fulfillment in Bosnia held in Rome on
June 14.
</P>
<P>
"Paris has offered a help in the matter of destruction of the
armaments through the way of OSCE, which has transmitted the offer
to all parties (of Bosnia)," said Doutriaux, who did not say if
the Muslims and Croats have accepted the offer.
</P>
<P>
"We are aware of the difficulties which the obligations of
destruction of the materials pose on some parties... Assistance by
France conforms with our conception of military stability in the
region which goes with a balance of forces at the lowest possible
level," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
