<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's CPPCC Chairman Meets Russian Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan said here today that there are many
reasons for furthering the sound Sino-Russian relations but there
is no excuse to make them retrogress or stagnate.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Stepanovich
Chernomyrdin here this afternoon, Li said that the Chinese leaders
have always viewed Sino-Russian ties as a pillar of China's
foreign affairs and extremely treasured the friendship and
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is willing to try all its best to push
forward the growth of its ties with Russia.
</P>
<P>
China is a country with the world's largest population, while
Russia with the biggest area, Li said, and the two countries share
a boundary line of more than 4,300 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, a long-term and stable good-neighborliness
and mutually beneficial cooperation between them are not only
helpful to their economic development and the improvement of their
people's life, but also serving their interests of maintaining
their own state sovereignty, opposing foreign interference and
maintaining peace and stability in Northeast Asia and even the
world.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China has made great achievements since it started
to implement the policy of reform and opening to the outside
world, but such achievements should by no means be overestimated.
</P>
<P>
China, with a backward basis, a large population and unbalanced
development, has a long way to go in its modernization drive, Li
said, and China is willing to learn from Russia in many regards
especially in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Over recent years, he said, exchange of visits at high levels
has become more frequent, and bilateral trade and economic
cooperation expanded. The two countries have supported each other
and maintained cooperation on many major domestic or international
issues, he added.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, he said, great potential is yet to be tapped in
furthering bilateral cooperation in various fields, and China
hopes the two countries will further their relations of mutual
trust, mutual understanding and supporting each other so as to
seek benefits as much as possible for their peoples.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that it is an unchangeable choice of Russia
to develop its friendship, cooperation and good-neighborliness
with China, and Russia is willing to make its greatest effort to
make the two countries good neighbors and partners.
</P>
<P>
Not everybody is happy with the sound relations between Russia
and China, the prime minister said, and therefore such relations
should be treasured and promoted in a positive way.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia and China should make joint efforts to
further develop their trade and economic cooperation, especially
in the space industry, energy and infrastructure in a bid to speed
their pace of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Following the meeting, Li gave an interview to local pressmen
and answered their questions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
