<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, S. Africa to Discuss Agricultural Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The final round of talks
between Zimbabwe and South Africa on a new agricultural trade
pact will be held next month, Co-Chairman of Zimbabwe's
Agricultural Negotiating Team, David Hasluck said here today.
</P>
<P>
Hasluck said his South African counterpart, Mfundu Nkulu, told him
last week that the final round of discussions would be held not later
than the first week of October.
</P>
<P>
''We are optimistic that we will find solutions to the outstanding
issues,'' said Hasluck, who is also Director of the Commercial Farmers
Union.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have already made progress on harmonisation of
veterinary, sanitary and phytosanitary regulations but were still to
agree on some veterinary control measures on beef. enditem

