<HEADLINE> Chinese Leaders Praise Sino-Yemeni Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leaders have praised
the past 40 years of friendly relations and cooperation between
China and Yemen and are looking forward to further expanding such
relations.
</P>
<P>
The praise was contained in two messages delivered to the
Yemeni side by Chinese Ambassador to Yemen Yu Xingzhi today, the
first from Chinese President Jiang Zemin to Yemeni Head of State
Ali Abdullah Saleh and the second from Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen to his Yemeni counterpart Abdul
Karim al-Iriyani.
</P>
<P>
The messages were conveyed on the occasion of the 40th
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between
China and Yemen, which falls on September 24.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ambassador conveyed the messages during a meeting
with Yemeni Deputy Foreign Minister Abdou Ali Abdul Rahman.
</P>
<P>
On the relations between the two friendly countries, the
messages say that in the past 40 years the ties of friendship and
cooperation have steadily developed in all fields as reflected in
bilateral contacts, mutual understanding, political support and
extensive economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two messages added that China and Yemen belong to the
developing countries, and that the further strengthening of
bilateral cooperation not only benefits the peoples of the
two countries but also contributes in promoting the cause of
peace and progress of mankind.
</P>
<P>
The two letters underlined that the ties of friendship and
cooperation between the two countries shall witness continuous
development through joint efforts of the governments and
peoples of the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
