<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Mexican Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The friendly
cooperation between China and Mexico not only conforms to the
interests of the two countries, but also benefits peace,
stability and development in Asia and the world as a whole,
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is here attending the 51st session of the United
Nations General Assembly, made the remarks during a meeting with
Mexican Foreign Minister Jose Angel Gurria Trevino at the U.N.
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders expressed their satisfaction over the growing
relations and frequent exchanges of high-level visits between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is also China's foreign minister, noted that the two
countries are engaged in effective cooperation in the fields of
economy, trade, science and technology, culture and education, as
well as the combat against drugs.
</P>
<P>
Qian appreciated Mexico's active role at the just concluded
96th Conference of the Inter-Parliamentary Union in Beijing and
its support to China on the issue of human rights and the Taiwan
question.
</P>
<P>
Qian said he hopes that the two countries will further
strengthen their exchanges and cooperation in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Angel Gurria agreed to Qian's views on bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also exchanged views on such aspects
as the APEC and the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, Qian said that Chinese President Jiang
Zemin is looking forward to Mexican President Ernesto Sedillo's
visit to China late this year.
</P>
<P>
Angel Gurria invited Qian to visit Mexico and Qian gladly
accepted the invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
