<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1630 GMT, September 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE -- The final round of talks between Zimbabwe and South
Africa on a new agricultural trade pact will be held next month,
Co-Chairman of Zimbabwe's Agricultural Negotiating Team, David
Hasluck said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan said
here Monday that there are many reasons for furthering the sound
Sino-Russian relations but there is no excuse to make them
retrogress or stagnate.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- A French military delegation arrived in Bosnia Monday
to help the Serbs and the Muslim-Croat Federation to destroy their
excessive heavy weapons in accordance with an agreement signed in
Vienna in June by Bosnia, Croatia and the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Through peace, cooperation, respect for human
rights and development, the U.N. has a major role to play in
preventing the division of the Cold War from finding new
expression in a widening gap in well-being, said Brazilian Foreign
Minister Luiz Felipe Lampreia Monday.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- Heavy exchanges of artillery, rocket and machine-gun
fires were reported from Sunday night to Monday morning on the
Zairean-Rwandan border between Bukavu, eastern Zaire, and
Cyangugu, southwest Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Two persons suspected to be involved in the
massive killing at a mosque in Multan, Pakistan, have been
arrested, a senior official said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe confirmed here
Monday that NATO will send follow-up peace-keeping forces to
Bosnia-Herzegovina after the present Implementation Force (IFOR)
finishes its mission on December 20.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab League (AL) welcomed Monday Qatar's decision
to postpone the opening of its representation mission in Israel
because of Israel's hardline policy on the Middle East peace
process. 
