<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Third Largest Recipient of UNICEF's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 23 (Xinhua) --The Ethiopian Minister of
Transport and Communication said today Ethiopia has been the
third largest recipient of United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF) after India and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion of the launching of the Ethiopian
commemorative stamp series marking UNICEF's 50th anniversary
here, Ethiopian Minister of Transport and Communication
Abdulmejid Hussein said the assistance amounts to 36 million
U.S.Dollars for the year 1996/97.
</P>
<P>
He said through the launching of the commemorative stamps
depicting immunization, breast-feeding, clear water and education
especially for girls, Ehtiopia is disseminating in the widest
possible way the message that these interventions are crucially
important.
</P>
<P>
The minister expressed Ethiopia's continuing effort to work
with UNICEF for the well-being of the Ethiopian children and
women.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on his part, UNICEF's representative in Ethiopia Rrn
Tuluhungwa said in accordance with UNICEF's 1996 state of the
world's children report, over the past 35 years, life expectancy
has risen in Ethiopia by 10 years.
</P>
<P>
He said during the same period infant mortality rate in the
country has decreased from 175 to the current 117 per 1,000 live
births, and that death from measles and whooping cough had
reduced by at least 30 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
