<HEADLINE> Suez Canal Offers Discount in Tolls to Vessels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Vessels carrying wheat from
Mediterranean ports and bound to the Jordanian port of Aqaba for
unloading are now granted a 10 percent discount in the Suez Canal
tolls.
</P>
<P>
The decision on the offer of discount took effect as of Sunday
night, Egypt's news agency MENA reported today.
</P>
<P>
For the vessels to benefit from the cut in the tolls, they
should obtain a certificate from the Aqaba port that they unloaded
their full shipment in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The ships will pay full tolls when they transit the canal to
Aqaba and will be given the discount in their return trip via the
canal, MENA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
