<HEADLINE> Egypt Exports 150,000 Tires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has exported 150,000
tires worth about 20 million Egyptian pounds (5.88 million
U.S. dollars) this year to a number of European, Arab and African
countries.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is now holding talks for concluding an agreement with
Canada to export to it car tires for the first time, Egypt's news
agency MENA reported today.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Husseiny, Director of the Egyptian Transport and
Engineering Company, was quoted as saying that Egypt is trying to
raise its annual production of tires to 2 million, of which
150,000 will be produced according to world specifications of
high speeds.
</P>
<P>
Egypt now produces some 1.7 million tires each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
