<HEADLINE> Two Policemen Shot Dead by Thugs in Kenyan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Armed robbers attacked a car
transporting money to the National Bank of Kenya here today,
killing two policemen escorting it.
</P>
<P>
The Nairobi Provincial Commissioner (PC), Francis Lekolool
said to reporters this evening that the two policemen, who were
shot alongside with the driver by five gangsters, were pronounced
dead on arrival at hospital.
</P>
<P>
The thugs struck at about 11:30 am at the turnoff of
Parliament Road, opposite to Intercontinental Hotel, where they
had strategically positioned themselves for the mission.
</P>
<P>
The PC said one gun was recovered at the scene while the other
was taken away by the thugs.
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made so far but the the police were in
hot pursuit of the thugs, Francis Lekolool added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
