<HEADLINE> Egypt, South Korea to Jointly Build Spinning Factory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and South Korea will
jointly build a fine spinning factory at Egypt's port city of
Suez, some 120 kilometers east of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
The work on the project will begin before the end of this year,
the Egyptian Middle East News Agency (MENA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The factory will have 30,000 spindles worth some 40 million
Egyptian pounds (11.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The total investments for the factory are estimated at about 70
million pounds (20.6 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The entire production of the factory will be exported to South
Korea, MENA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
