<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4th Pan African Conference of Red Cross Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has commended the International Committee of the Red
Cross for working in difficult political and physical conditions.
</P>
<P>
The president made the commendation in a speech read for him
by Prime Minister Kintu Musoke while opening the five-day 4th Pan
African Confernce of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies here
today.
</P>
<P>
Museveni observed that the Red Cross has in recent years given
assistance to a million refugees from Rwanda and Burundi. The
association also gave assistance to another million Mozambican
refugees in Malawi.
</P>
<P>
The president said the catalog of man-made disasters started
with massive and devastating extraction of human resources
through slavery to the west and east of the continent.
</P>
<P>
Museveni therefore expressed gratitude to the humanitarian
assistance given by the international community, and particularly
the International Federation of the Red Cross and Red Crescent
Societies.
</P>
<P>
Talking about Uganda, the president said that the Uganda Red
Cross has benefited through the recently completed Arua branch
modern office and residential block complex at Koboko in northern
Uganda, where hundreds of refugees from Sudan have been
accommodated for the last four years.
</P>
<P>
The president said the agenda from now on into the 21st
century should be to promote viable and relevant linkages, adding
the 21st century must be one of total development.
</P>
<P>
Mmuseveni observed that today millions of people in Africa
lack the bare necessities for survival, adding that the
inequalities between the rich and the poor are constantly
increasing.
</P>
<P>
He said thousands of persons are victims of discrimination,
like Africans who exist at the periphery of the developed
countries.
</P>
<P>
He asserted that Africa's vulnerability has mainly been a
result of man-made disasters due to lack of viable mechanism of
conflict prevention and resolution.
</P>
<P>
He called for the strengthening of regional, continental and
international organisations to address conflict prevention and
resolution more effectively.
</P>
<P>
He called for a study of the root causes of the problems to
find durable solutions to them.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was also addressed by President of Uganda
Red Cross Society Bishop Baharagate, President of the
International Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies Mario
Villarroel Lander and Vice President of the International
Committee of the Red Cross Eric Roethlisberger. enditem

