<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen: China Supports Macedonia's Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China attaches
importance to its friendly cooperation with Macedonia and supports
the latter's independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is also China's foreign minister, made the statement
during his meeting with Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov at the
United Nations headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the Chinese government respects the Macedonian
people's choice for their own social system and way of
development, and the Macedonian government's foreign and domestic
policies.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries support each other on many
issues and the Chinese government is thankful for Macedonia's
"one-China" position on the Taiwan question.
</P>
<P>
While stating that it is Macedonia's consistent policy to hold
the "one-China" position, President Gligorov expressed his
appreciation of China's stand on independence and
self-determination in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated China's position on treating each other on
an equal footing in international relations and expressed his
thanks for China's support to his nation.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov said his country attaches importance to the
development of friendly relations with China and he is happy to
see the smooth growth of cooperation between the two sides in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov briefed Qian on his government's efforts in the
settlement of the crisis of the former Yugoslavia and the
establishment of good ties with its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Qian said he is confident that Macedonia will continue to make
active contributions to peace, stability and development in the
Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that the two nations should increase
exchanges in various fields including high-level visits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
