<HEADLINE> Egypt Describes Israel's Statements on Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Egypt said today that Israel's
rhetoric on the Middle East peace process is "dinosaurian" because
it completely contradicts with the logic of present realities.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the recent statements made by Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to the German magazine Der Spiegel,
Assistant Foreign Minister Fathi el-Shazli said that the Israeli
rhetoric also contradicts with the fact that Israel is a party to
the peace process and is "disgusting."
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu told the magazine that there will not be a
Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
In reference to Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai's
remarks in which he warned Syria against the redeployment of its
forces in Lebanon, Shazli said that Israel's threatening to resort
to military options can never help create the favorable atmosphere
for the success of any peaceful effort and will only have tragic
reactions.
</P>
<P>
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad have said that the Syrian
forces' moves in Lebanon do not imply any threats from Syria to
other parties.
</P>
<P>
Shazli told reporters that Netanyahu's government is unaware of
the dangers of the failure of the Middle East peace process because of
the negative Israeli practices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
