<HEADLINE> Iran Expels Tajik Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Ministry today
issue an order to expel Tashmet Nazirov, Tajikistan's charge
d'affaires in Tehran, to leave Iran in 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry called Tashmet Nazirov as a persona non
grata on charge of being engaged in activities not compatible with
his diplomatic status.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that Gholamreza
Baqeri, head of the second department for former Soviet
Republic affairs, today summoned the Tajik charge d'affaires to
the Foreign Ministry and handed him the expulsion order.
</P>
<P>
However, IRNA gave no detail about the expulsion order and
the reason leading to the expulsion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
