<HEADLINE> Qian: China to Push Sino-Ethiopian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China is willing to
further enhance its traditional friendship and cooperation with
Ethiopia, Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also Chinese foreign minister, made the remarks during a
meeting with his Ethiopian counterpart, Seyoum Mesfin, at the
United Nations headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted the smooth development of relations and successful
cooperation in various fields between China and Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
He said the successful visit by Chinese President Jiang Zemin
to Ethiopia in May and the China-tour by Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi last year have laid a strong foundation to the
all-round development of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Qian appreciated Ethiopia's "one China" policy and the support
to China on the issue of human rights.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated Ethiopia's contributions in the African and
regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Seyoum agreed with Qian's views on the bilateral ties and added
that Ethiopia was satisfied with the growth of friendly ties
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He affirmed China's constructive role in the international and
regional affairs and said China has a special position in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Seyoum introduced to Qian Africa's situation and the African
nations' efforts in resolving regional problems.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed China's satisfaction over African people's
progress in their development and said China hopes that related
regions in Africa could, through dialogues, reduce their
differences, eliminate the root of instability and maintain
stability so as to achieve development," said the Chinese leader.
</P>
</TEXT>
