<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Strongly Condemns Hegemony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign
Minister Ali-Akbar Velayati today strongly condemned hegemony
which flouts justice, freedom, participation, rule of law,
tolerance, human rights, pluralism and democracy in a dangerous
and unprecedented manner.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the first day of the general debate of the 51st
session of the U.N. General Assembly, Velayati said that
concurrent with the expansion of participatory democracy in many
countries, a complex movement has emerged toward international
autocracy and totalitarianism.
</P>
<P>
The evident behavioral characteristics of this menace can be
summerized as following:
</P>
<P>
-- unilateralism: total lack of commitment to mutual
cooperation and common solutions, and complete reliance on
unilateral measures in various fields;
</P>
<P>
-- opportunism: resort to international forum only as mechanisms
for promotion of national self-interest and often in pursuit of
domestic agenda;
</P>
<P>
-- secrecy; insistence on dogmatic, non-transparent and closed
methods and rejection of transparency;
</P>
<P>
-- lawlessness: evasion of the rule of law coupled with
audacity in breaking the law and universal norms, even in public
and official manner;
</P>
<P>
-- imposition: promotion of domestic agenda and national
priorities through imposition of policies on others, including
through extra-territorial application of domestic legislation; and
</P>
<P>
-- coercion: unbridled resort to the threat and use of force in
international political, economic and commercial relations.
</P>
<P>
However, the most notable manifestation of the new
international totalitarianism surfaces in the cultural sphere, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Our world is one characterized by diversity of religions,
civilizations, cultures and customs. This diversity has naturally
resulted in the emergence of many systems of law and values, with
similarities as well as differences," he said.
</P>
<P>
Regrettably, the claimants of world leadership have either
failed to grasp this self-evident reality due to their own lack of
historical and cultural depth or have found it incompatible with
their interests and thereby attempt to neglect it, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the international community to condemn and reject
all forms of terrorism, regardless of the identity of victims or
perpetrators, and irrespective of their political tendencies and
objectives.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
