<HEADLINE> Five People Killed in Highway Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A truck slammed into a car
that had stopped behind a school bus on a fog-shrouded highway
Monday, smashing the car underneath the bus and killing five
people, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The bus had been carrying students for the Rosendale-Brandon
School District, Wisconsin, said Fond du Lac County sheriff's Sgt.
Mike Thome, The Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said five people died. A local radio station said
one of the victims was a high school student. The other four,
including a 7-year-old girl who died later at a hospital, were in
the smashed car.
</P>
<P>
Eleven children aged 7 to 15 were taken to St. Agnes Hospital
in Fond du Lac, and all were treated for minor injuries and
released.
</P>
<P>
A man and a woman were in stable condition at a hospital.
</P>
</TEXT>
