<HEADLINE> Tyson Testifies in Federal Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson testified in
court on Monday that he got mad with former trainer Kevin Rooney
after the latter unveiled his personal life to media.
</P>
<P>
Sued for breach of contract, Tyson stood in the federal court
in Albany for three hours in a case filed by Rooney for 49 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rooney, who started his first training with Tyson in 1982, said
Tyson had broken his word by firing him after the death of mentor
Cus D'Amato in 1985.
</P>
<P>
According to Tyson, he had taken Rooney as a brother of his
family until the former trainer talked too much about his marriage
with actress Robin Givens.
</P>
<P>
After Rooney's criticism went public in media, Tyson got angry
and fired the former trainer.
</P>
<P>
In the case, Rooney was suing the boxer for 18.5 million
dollars of his past earnings and 30.6 million dollars in projected
earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
