<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Industry Becomes Pillar of Yantai Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Hi-tech industry in China's
port city Yantai has become a leader in the local economy, a
government official there said recently.
</P>
<P>
Yantai, in east China's Shandong Province, has established 406
enterprises that develop or manufacture hi-tech products,
accounting for a quarter of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech enterprises generated a total output value of 6.2
billion yuan (about 747 million US dollars) and 1.6 billion yuan
in taxes and profits last year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Yantai has implemented the strategy of
"invigorating the city's economy through science and technology,"
and has given favorable treatment to hi-tech enterprises in land
use, funding, power supply and intelligence.
</P>
<P>
Large state-owned enterprises have pioneered the development of
hi-tech industries. The city has selected 100 enterprises to
upgrade traditional industries and old products.
</P>
<P>
The Yantai Wanhua Synthetic Leather Group Company has broken
the monopoly of foreign technology in the development of
high-grade imitation synthetic leather.
</P>
<P>
By keeping up-to-date with the latest global developments in
technology, the Polaris Clock Corporation has become the largest
clock company in China.
</P>
<P>
Technology-intensive joint ventures have also sprung up in the
city. Most of the 150 projects boast state-of-the-art technology,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
Yantai presently has one of the four largest manufacturing
bases of transparent electric conduction glass in the world, which
was formed in cooperation with an American company.
</P>
<P>
By cooperating with another US company, the city has produced a
special sealing gum, which satisfies 90 percent of the demand of
the country's market.
</P>
<P>
Yantai has also cooperated with a Japanese company for the
production of automobile air conditioners. The city also joined
hands with a company from the Republic of Korea to make
excavators, a project that is expected to generate an output value
of one billion US dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises also play an active role in the
development of hi-tech products. Household appliances developed by
the Hongxiang Company sells well in the overseas market. Last
year, the company turned out a production volume of 1.3 billion
yuan. And Zhichu Group, a village-run company, has developed 28
hi-tech products.
</P>
<P>
The city has set up 450 hi-tech industries, covering the fields
of electronic information, integration of machinery and
electronics, new materials, bio-engineering, mechanics, medicine,
and household appliances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
