<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kite Flying Fuels Take-off of Weifang Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Kite-flying, a hobby that
dates back 2,500 years in Weifang, has helped the local economy
take off.
</P>
<P>
The east China city has hosted 13 kite flying festivals since
1984, which have attracted large sums of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Weifang brought in 443 million US dollars of overseas
capital, more than double the amount in 1992.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995, the city had used 3.2 billion yuan (about
386 million US dollars) of overseas investment and more than 1,300
overseas enterprises had been set up in the city.
</P>
<P>
Output value of the city soared from five billion to 40 billion
yuan during the 1983-1994 period, said a leading city official.
</P>
<P>
At the 12th International Kite Flying Festival in 1995, 2,000
businessmen from 29 countries and regions concluded 2,200 projects
with the city, located in Shandong Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
