<HEADLINE> Jamaica Defeats St. Vincent in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Jamaica defeated St
Vincent 2-1 in an away game in Kingstown, St Vincent on Monday as
the two vied for spots in the 1998 World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
In one of three semifinal groups, Jamaica ranked first in Group
three with two straight wins while St. Vincent tailed by losing
two games in a row.
</P>
<P>
Paul Young scored the two for Jamaica, all in the first half,
before Christopher Harry netted a penalty in the 81st minute.
</P>
<P>
The two Caribbean teams will meet again on November 10 at
Kingston.
</P>
<P>
From three four-team semifinals, three teams will qualify from
CONCACAF, the regional body for North and Central America and the
Caribbean, for the World Cup finals in France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
