<HEADLINE> China Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China will strengthen its anti-poverty campaign to meet the
country's goal of eliminating poverty by the end of this century,
and efforts toward this end "will not be shaken," said Chinese
president Jiang Zemin at a national conference on poverty
alleviation, which opened Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng told conference participants that the
country's poor areas should list poverty relief high on their
economic development plan, and assign the task of providing enough
food and clothing to the masses as the first priority.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the country will contribute more to the campaign
and adopt measures to use relief funds more efficiently.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese president Jiang Zemin said that the government shall
never forget people in the former revolutionary bases who had made
great contribution to the victory of Chinese revolutionary.
</P>
<P>
During his recent inspection along the Beijing-Kowloon Railway,
he said that poverty must be eliminated within this century. China
currently has 65 million people living in poverty. Many of many
live in former revolutionary bases.
</P>
<P>
-- One million pots of flowers and over 50 large floral
terraces will be on display in the streets of China's capital to
celebrate National Day, which falls on October 1. This year is the
47th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Environmental protection is "the key for China to sustain
economic development," the country's strategic task, State
Councillor Song Jian affirmed Monday.
</P>
<P>
Though much progress has been made in environment protection,
the overall situation in China is still grave, said Song at the
fifth meeting of the China Council for International Cooperation
on Environment and Development. He said investment should be
increased to finance environment projects through all possible
channels.  
</P>
