<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Girls Detained for Alleged Killing of Old Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Two sisters aged 10 and
13 have been detained in the capital city for beating an old man
to death, police said today.
</P>
<P>
The victim, Policarpo Romero, died on September 14 in a clinic
in the Villa Caraza area of Buenos Aires, one week after being
admitted with battery injuries to the head, arms and legs.
</P>
<P>
Previously, he lived with his sister, Irma Romero, and was a
neighbor of the two girls, whose identities have not been
revealed, as required by law.
</P>
<P>
A week before September 14, both girls went into the old man's
home while his sister was out.
</P>
<P>
When she returned home, Romero found her brother lying in bed
with wounds to the head and the rest of his body, and that the
house had been ransacked with her money and valuables missing.
</P>
<P>
When the two girls were detained, the police found in their
house bed sheets, perfumes and other objects which Romero claimed
to be hers.
</P>
<P>
The police are investigating to determine if the girls' motive
for killing the old man was robbery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
