<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qatar Nips Philippines in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, September 23 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Qatar scored five goals
against nil, all in the first half, for a clear victory against
the Philippines at a World Cup Asian group 10 qualifier here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Salem al-Enazi netted twice, including the opener in
the 18th minute with his second scored in the 41st minute.
</P>
<P>
The other goals were converted through Mohammad Soufi, Adel
Khamis and Abdul Aziz Hassan in a span of 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Up till now, Qatar won all two games for six points, topping
the four-member group wherein the Philippines tailed with two
straight games.
</P>
<P>
Winner of the group will vie against other nine group winners
in a single round-robin two-group second round competitions.
</P>
<P>
Second-round winners and runners-up will advance to the two-leg
play-off third round, wherein winners qualify for the World Cup
Finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The winners in the losers' play-offs will enter two-leg
play-offs with Oceania winner for another berth for the 1998
finals.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Asian group qualifiers will be played in 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
