<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telephone Anti-Fakes Electronic Code System in Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech system that uses
secret codes to combat fake goods in China is to go national after
a successful trial operation.
</P>
<P>
The system, invented by Chinese experts, uses a telephone
network and electronic codes to identify genuine articles. A
national work conference called to discuss the system has been
told it is to be spread nationwide after proving successful.
</P>
<P>
Its trial operation in parts of the country since January this
year received positive response from users.
</P>
<P>
China Anti-Fakes Association is entrusted by the State Bureau
of Technical Supervision to popularize it throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Tenglong Anti-Fake Technology Company, which is based in
Haikou, provincial capital of Hainan in South China, is
responsible for implementing the project.
</P>
<P>
The system, based on computerized data banks and the national
computerized telephone information retrieval network, will provide
manufacturers of quality products with special data codes and
secret codes.
</P>
<P>
Commodity dealers or buyers can check up the goods they have
purchased by telephone, after tearing off the cover on the codes.
</P>
<P>
Since it is a hi-tech system, it is impossible for anyone to
produce fake codes, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan-based company has invested 40 million yuan to set up
a data bank capable of holding 50 billion different electronic
codes. Terminals will be built in major cities across the country.
</P>
<P>
Some experts say the network will help protect quality and
brand-famed products in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
