<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Machine-Builders in Northeast Win Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Machinery
plans to finance major machine-building plants in northeast China
to help them launch technological upgrade projects.
</P>
<P>
The aim is to boost the fortunes of an important sector that
employs a quarter of all the area's workers.
</P>
<P>
The companies to receive government assistance will include
manufacturers of power generation, transformers and transmission
facilities, lathe-builders and suppliers of important fittings and
parts in the bearing industry.
</P>
<P>
The funding will also be granted to manufacturers of light and
heavy automotives, according to Deputy Minister Sun Changji, who
was recently interviewed by Xinhua in Liaoning coastal city Dalian.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, 104 such projects have been approved
by the ministry, involving a total investment of 5.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The northeastern region normally covers Heilongjiang, Jilin and
Liaoning, as well as the eastern part of Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region. The area is an old industrial base of the country.
</P>
<P>
The machinery industry makes up 25.73 percent of the region's
total industrial production value.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has urged the machinery sector in the northeast to
carry out ideological and managerial reforms to revive the old
industrial base.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
