<DOCNO> XIE19960924.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Expected to Produces Record 46 Million tons of Fruit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to produce
a record 46 million tons of fruit this year, greatly easing the
country's fruit shortage.
</P>
<P>
Supply sources say that the present time is the peak season for
the fruit harvest, and a survey shows there will be a bumper
harvest, which may in turn ease the fruit supply and help cut
prices.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade or so the reform and opening-up policy has
led to fruit production enjoying a fast growth.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995 fruit plantation areas reached eight
million hectares, with an annual production of 42.14 million tons,
20.4 percent over that of 1994.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that as the country's fruit production may top
46 million tons, fruit supply shortages will ease with the good
prospect of cheaper prices in shops and markets for buyers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
